var book = {
	"name": "Ecclesiastes",
	"numChapters": 12,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>The words of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17317A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17317A\"></sup>Preacher, the son of David, king in Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17318B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17318B\"></sup>Vanity of vanities,” says the Preacher,“Vanity of vanities! All is vanity.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17319C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17319C\"></sup>What advantage does man have in all his workWhich he does under the sun?",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>A generation goes and a generation comes,But the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17320D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17320D\"></sup>earth remains forever.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Also, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17321E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17321E\"></sup>the sun rises and the sun sets;And hastening to its place it rises there <i>again</i>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17322F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17322F\"></sup>Blowing toward the south,Then turning toward the north,The wind continues swirling along;And on its circular courses the wind returns.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>All the rivers flow into the sea,Yet the sea is not full.To the place where the rivers flow,There they flow again.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>All things are wearisome;Man is not able to tell <i>it</i>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17324G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17324G\"></sup>The eye is not satisfied with seeing,Nor is the ear filled with hearing.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17325H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17325H\"></sup>That which has been is that which will be,And that which has been done is that which will be done.So there is nothing new under the sun.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Is there anything of which one might say,“See this, it is new”?Already it has existed for agesWhich were before us.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>There is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17327I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17327I\"></sup>no remembrance of earlier things;And also of the later things which will occur,There will be for them no remembranceAmong those who will come later <i>still</i>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>I, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17328J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17328J\"></sup>Preacher, have been king over Israel in Jerusalem.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17329K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17329K\"></sup>set my mind to seek and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17329L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17329L\"></sup>explore by wisdom concerning all that has been done under heaven. <i>It</i> is a grievous <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17329M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17329M\"></sup>task <i>which</i> God has given to the sons of men to be afflicted with.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>I have seen all the works which have been done under the sun, and behold, all is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17330N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17330N\"></sup>vanity and striving after wind.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>What is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17331O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17331O\"></sup>crooked cannot be straightened and what is lacking cannot be counted.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>I said to myself, “Behold, I have magnified and increased <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17332P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17332P\"></sup>wisdom more than all who were over Jerusalem before me; and my mind has observed a wealth of wisdom and knowledge.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17333Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17333Q\"></sup>set my mind to know wisdom and to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17333R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17333R\"></sup>know madness and folly; I realized that this also is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17333S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17333S\"></sup>striving after wind.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17334T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17334T\"></sup>in much wisdom there is much grief, and increasing knowledge <i>results in</i> increasing pain."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>I said to myself, “Come now, I will test you with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17335A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17335A\"></sup>pleasure. So enjoy yourself.” And behold, it too was futility.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17336B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17336B\"></sup>I said of laughter, “It is madness,” and of pleasure, “What does it accomplish?”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I explored with my mind <i>how</i> to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17337C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17337C\"></sup>stimulate my body with wine while my mind was guiding <i>me</i> wisely, and how to take hold of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17337D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17337D\"></sup>folly, until I could see <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17337E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17337E\"></sup>what good there is for the sons of men to do under heaven the few years of their lives.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I enlarged my works: I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17338F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17338F\"></sup>built houses for myself, I planted <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17338G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17338G\"></sup>vineyards for myself;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17339H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17339H\"></sup>gardens and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17339I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17339I\"></sup>parks for myself and I planted in them all kinds of fruit trees;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17340J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17340J\"></sup>ponds of water for myself from which to irrigate a forest of growing trees.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I bought male and female slaves and I had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17341K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17341K\"></sup>homeborn slaves. Also I possessed flocks and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17341L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17341L\"></sup>herds larger than all who preceded me in Jerusalem.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Also, I collected for myself silver and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17342M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17342M\"></sup>gold and the treasure of kings and provinces. I provided for myself <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17342N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17342N\"></sup>male and female singers and the pleasures of men—many concubines.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then I became <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17343O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17343O\"></sup>great and increased more than all who preceded me in Jerusalem. My wisdom also stood by me.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17344P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17344P\"></sup>All that my eyes desired I did not refuse them. I did not withhold my heart from any pleasure, for my heart was pleased because of all my labor and this was my <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17344Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17344Q\"></sup>reward for all my labor.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Thus I considered all my activities which my hands had done and the labor which I had exerted, and behold all was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17345R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17345R\"></sup>vanity and striving after wind and there was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17345S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17345S\"></sup>no profit under the sun.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So I turned to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17346T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17346T\"></sup>consider wisdom, madness and folly; for what <i>will</i> the man <i>do</i> who will come after the king <i>except</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17346U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17346U\"></sup>what has already been done?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And I saw that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17347V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17347V\"></sup>wisdom excels folly as light excels darkness.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The wise man’s eyes are in his head, but the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17348W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17348W\"></sup>fool walks in darkness. And yet I know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17348X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17348X\"></sup>one fate befalls them both.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then I said to myself, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17349Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17349Y\"></sup>As is the fate of the fool, it will also befall me. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17349Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17349Z\"></sup>Why then have I been extremely wise?” So I said to myself, “This too is vanity.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For there is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17350AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17350AA\"></sup>no lasting remembrance of the wise man <i>as</i> with the fool, inasmuch as <i>in</i> the coming days all will be forgotten. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17350AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17350AB\"></sup>how the wise man and the fool alike die!",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17351AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17351AC\"></sup>hated life, for the work which had been done under the sun was grievous to me; because everything is futility and striving after wind.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Thus I hated <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17352AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17352AD\"></sup>all the fruit of my labor for which I had labored under the sun, for I must <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17352AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17352AE\"></sup>leave it to the man who will come after me.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And who knows whether he will be a wise man or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17353AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17353AF\"></sup>a fool? Yet he will have control over all the fruit of my labor for which I have labored by acting wisely under the sun. This too is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17353AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17353AG\"></sup>vanity.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Therefore I completely despaired of all the fruit of my labor for which I had labored under the sun.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When there is a man who has labored with wisdom, knowledge and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17355AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17355AH\"></sup>skill, then he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17355AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17355AI\"></sup>gives his legacy to one who has not labored with them. This too is vanity and a great evil.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For what does a man get in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17356AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17356AJ\"></sup>all his labor and in his striving with which he labors under the sun?",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Because all his days his task is painful and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17357AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17357AK\"></sup>grievous; even at night his mind <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17357AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17357AL\"></sup>does not rest. This too is vanity.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>There is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17358AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17358AM\"></sup>nothing better for a man <i>than</i> to eat and drink and tell himself that his labor is good. This also I have seen that it is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17358AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17358AN\"></sup>from the hand of God.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>For who can eat and who can have enjoyment without Him?",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>For to a person who is good in His sight <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17360AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17360AO\"></sup>He has given wisdom and knowledge and joy, while to the sinner He has given the task of gathering and collecting so that he may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17360AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17360AP\"></sup>give to one who is good in God’s sight. This too is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17360AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17360AQ\"></sup>vanity and striving after wind."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>There is an appointed time for everything. And there is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17361A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17361A\"></sup>time for every event under heaven—",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>A time to give birth and a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17362B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17362B\"></sup>time to die;A time to plant and a time to uproot what is planted.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>A <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17363C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17363C\"></sup>time to kill and a time to heal;A time to tear down and a time to build up.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>A time to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17364D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17364D\"></sup>weep and a time to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17364E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17364E\"></sup>laugh;A time to mourn and a time to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17364F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17364F\"></sup>dance.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>A time to throw stones and a time to gather stones;A time to embrace and a time to shun embracing.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>A time to search and a time to give up as lost;A time to keep and a time to throw away.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>A time to tear apart and a time to sew together;A time to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17367G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17367G\"></sup>be silent and a time to speak.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>A time to love and a time to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17368H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17368H\"></sup>hate;A time for war and a time for peace.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17369I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17369I\"></sup>What profit is there to the worker from that in which he toils?",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>I have seen the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17370J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17370J\"></sup>task which God has given the sons of men with which to occupy themselves.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17371K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17371K\"></sup>made everything appropriate in its time. He has also set eternity in their heart, yet so that man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17371L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17371L\"></sup>will not find out the work which God has done from the beginning even to the end.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>I know that there is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17372M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17372M\"></sup>nothing better for them than to rejoice and to do good in one’s lifetime;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>moreover, that every man who eats and drinks sees good in all his labor—it is the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17373N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17373N\"></sup>gift of God.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>I know that everything God does will remain forever; there is nothing to add to it and there is nothing to take from it, for God has <i>so</i> worked that men should <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17374O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17374O\"></sup>fear Him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>That <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17375P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17375P\"></sup>which is has been already and that which will be has already been, for God seeks what has passed by.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Furthermore, I have seen under the sun <i>that</i> in the place of justice there is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17376Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17376Q\"></sup>wickedness and in the place of righteousness there is wickedness.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I said to myself, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17377R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17377R\"></sup>God will judge both the righteous man and the wicked man,” for a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17377S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17377S\"></sup>time for every matter and for every deed is there.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>I said to myself concerning the sons of men, “God has surely tested them in order for them to see that they are but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17378T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17378T\"></sup>beasts.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17379U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17379U\"></sup>For the fate of the sons of men and the fate of beasts is the same. As one dies so dies the other; indeed, they all have the same breath and there is no advantage for man over beast, for all is vanity.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>All go to the same place. All came from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17380V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17380V\"></sup>dust and all return to the dust.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Who knows that the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17381W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17381W\"></sup>breath of man ascends upward and the breath of the beast descends downward to the earth?",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>I have seen that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17382X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17382X\"></sup>nothing is better than that man should be happy in his activities, for that is his lot. For who will bring him to see <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17382Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17382Y\"></sup>what will occur after him?"
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>Then I looked again at all the acts of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17383A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17383A\"></sup>oppression which were being done under the sun. And behold <i>I saw</i> the tears of the oppressed and <i>that</i> they had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17383B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17383B\"></sup>no one to comfort <i>them</i>; and on the side of their oppressors was power, but they had no one to comfort <i>them</i>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17384C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17384C\"></sup>I congratulated the dead who are already dead more than the living who are still living.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17385D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17385D\"></sup>better <i>off</i> than both of them is the one who has never existed, who has never seen the evil activity that is done under the sun.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I have seen that every labor and every <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17386E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17386E\"></sup>skill which is done is <i>the result of</i> rivalry between a man and his neighbor. This too is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17386F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17386F\"></sup>vanity and striving after wind.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The fool <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17387G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17387G\"></sup>folds his hands and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17387H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17387H\"></sup>consumes his own flesh.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>One hand full of rest is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17388I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17388I\"></sup>better than two fists full of labor and striving after wind.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then I looked again at vanity under the sun.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>There was a certain man without a dependent, having neither a son nor a brother, yet there was no end to all his labor. Indeed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17390J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17390J\"></sup>his eyes were not satisfied with riches <i>and he never asked</i>, “And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17390K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17390K\"></sup>for whom am I laboring and depriving myself of pleasure?” This too is vanity and it is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17390L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17390L\"></sup>grievous task.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Two are better than one because they have a good return for their labor.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For if either of them falls, the one will lift up his companion. But woe to the one who falls when there is not another to lift him up.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Furthermore, if two lie down together they keep warm, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17393M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17393M\"></sup>how can one be warm <i>alone</i>?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And if one can overpower him who is alone, two can resist him. A cord of three <i>strands</i> is not quickly torn apart.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>A <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17395N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17395N\"></sup>poor yet wise lad is better than an old and foolish king who no longer knows <i>how</i> to receive instruction.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>For he has come <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17396O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17396O\"></sup>out of prison to become king, even though he was born poor in his kingdom.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>I have seen all the living under the sun throng to the side of the second lad who replaces him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>There is no end to all the people, to all who were before them, and even the ones who will come later will not be happy with him, for this too is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17398P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17398P\"></sup>vanity and striving after wind."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17399A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17399A\"></sup>Guard your steps as you go to the house of God and draw near to listen rather than to offer the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17399B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17399B\"></sup>sacrifice of fools; for they do not know they are doing evil.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Do not be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17400C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17400C\"></sup>hasty in word or impulsive in thought to bring up a matter in the presence of God. For God is in heaven and you are on the earth; therefore let your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17400D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17400D\"></sup>words be few.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For the dream comes through much effort and the voice of a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17401E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17401E\"></sup>fool through many words.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17402F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17402F\"></sup>make a vow to God, do not be late in paying it; for <i>He takes</i> no delight in fools. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17402G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17402G\"></sup>Pay what you vow!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>It is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17403H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17403H\"></sup>better that you should not vow than that you should vow and not pay.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Do not let your speech cause you to sin and do not say in the presence of the messenger <i>of God</i> that it was a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17404I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17404I\"></sup>mistake. Why should God be angry on account of your voice and destroy the work of your hands?",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For in many dreams and in many words there is emptiness. Rather, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17405J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17405J\"></sup>fear God.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>If you see <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17406K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17406K\"></sup>oppression of the poor and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17406L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17406L\"></sup>denial of justice and righteousness in the province, do not be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17406M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17406M\"></sup>shocked at the sight; for one official watches over another official, and there are higher officials over them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>After all, a king who cultivates the field is an advantage to the land.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17408N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17408N\"></sup>He who loves money will not be satisfied with money, nor he who loves abundance <i>with its</i> income. This too is vanity.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17409O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17409O\"></sup>When good things increase, those who consume them increase. So what is the advantage to their owners except to look on?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The sleep of the working man is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17410P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17410P\"></sup>pleasant, whether he eats little or much; but the full stomach of the rich man does not allow him to sleep.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>There is a grievous evil <i>which</i> I have seen under the sun: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17411Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17411Q\"></sup>riches being hoarded by their owner to his hurt.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When those riches were lost through a bad investment and he had fathered a son, then there was nothing to support him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17413R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17413R\"></sup>As he had come naked from his mother’s womb, so will he return as he came. He will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17413S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17413S\"></sup>take nothing from the fruit of his labor that he can carry in his hand.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>This also is a grievous evil—exactly as a man is born, thus will he die. So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17414T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17414T\"></sup>what is the advantage to him who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17414U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17414U\"></sup>toils for the wind?",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Throughout his life <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17415V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17415V\"></sup><i>he</i> also eats in darkness with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17415W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17415W\"></sup>great vexation, sickness and anger.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Here is what I have seen to be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17416X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17416X\"></sup>good and fitting: to eat, to drink and enjoy oneself in all one’s labor in which he toils under the sun <i>during</i> the few years of his life which God has given him; for this is his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17416Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17416Y\"></sup>reward.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Furthermore, as for every man to whom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17417Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17417Z\"></sup>God has given riches and wealth, He has also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17417AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17417AA\"></sup>empowered him to eat from them and to receive his reward and rejoice in his labor; this is the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17417AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17417AB\"></sup>gift of God.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>For he will not often consider the years of his life, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17418AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17418AC\"></sup>God keeps him occupied with the gladness of his heart."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>There is an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17419A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17419A\"></sup>evil which I have seen under the sun and it is prevalent among men—",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>a man to whom God has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17420B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17420B\"></sup>given riches and wealth and honor so that his soul <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17420C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17420C\"></sup>lacks nothing of all that he desires; yet God has not empowered him to eat from them, for a foreigner enjoys them. This is vanity and a severe affliction.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>If a man fathers a hundred <i>children</i> and lives many years, however many they be, but his soul is not satisfied with good things and he does not even have a <i>proper</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17421D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17421D\"></sup>burial, <i>then</i> I say, “Better <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17421E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17421E\"></sup>the miscarriage than he,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>for it comes in futility and goes into obscurity; and its name is covered in obscurity.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>It never sees the sun and it never knows <i>anything</i>; it is better off than he.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Even if the <i>other</i> man lives a thousand years twice and does not enjoy good things—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17424F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17424F\"></sup>do not all go to one place?”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17425G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17425G\"></sup>All a man’s labor is for his mouth and yet the appetite is not satisfied.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17426H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17426H\"></sup>what advantage does the wise man have over the fool? What <i>advantage</i> does the poor man have, knowing <i>how</i> to walk before the living?",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>What the eyes <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17427I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17427I\"></sup>see is better than what the soul desires. This too is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17427J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17427J\"></sup>futility and a striving after wind.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Whatever <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17428K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17428K\"></sup>exists has already been named, and it is known what man is; for he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17428L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17428L\"></sup>cannot dispute with him who is stronger than he is.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>For there are many words which increase futility. What <i>then</i> is the advantage to a man?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For who knows what is good for a man during <i>his</i> lifetime, <i>during</i> the few years of his futile life? He will spend them like a shadow. For who can tell a man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17430M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17430M\"></sup>what will be after him under the sun?"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>A <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17431A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17431A\"></sup>good name is better than a good ointment,And the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17431B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17431B\"></sup>day of <i>one’s</i> death is better than the day of one’s birth.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>It is better to go to a house of mourningThan to go to a house of feasting,Because that is the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17432C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17432C\"></sup>end of every man,And the living <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17432D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17432D\"></sup>takes <i>it</i> to heart.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17433E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17433E\"></sup>Sorrow is better than laughter,For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17433F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17433F\"></sup>when a face is sad a heart may be happy.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The mind of the wise is in the house of mourning,While the mind of fools is in the house of pleasure.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>It is better to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17435G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17435G\"></sup>listen to the rebuke of a wise manThan for one to listen to the song of fools.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For as the crackling of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17436H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17436H\"></sup>thorn bushes under a pot,So is the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17436I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17436I\"></sup>laughter of the fool;And this too is futility.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17437J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17437J\"></sup>oppression makes a wise man mad,And a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17437K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17437K\"></sup>bribe corrupts the heart.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17438L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17438L\"></sup>end of a matter is better than its beginning;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17438M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17438M\"></sup>Patience of spirit is better than haughtiness of spirit.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Do not be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17439N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17439N\"></sup>eager in your heart to be angry,For anger resides in the bosom of fools.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Do not say, “Why is it that the former days were better than these?”For it is not from wisdom that you ask about this.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Wisdom along with an inheritance is goodAnd an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17441O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17441O\"></sup>advantage to those who see the sun.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17442P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17442P\"></sup>wisdom is protection <i>just as</i> money is protection,But the advantage of knowledge is that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17442Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17442Q\"></sup>wisdom preserves the lives of its possessors.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Consider the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17443R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17443R\"></sup>work of God,For who is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17443S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17443S\"></sup>able to straighten what He has bent?",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17444T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17444T\"></sup>In the day of prosperity be happy,But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17444U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17444U\"></sup>in the day of adversity consider—God has made the one as well as the otherSo that man will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17444V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17444V\"></sup>not discover anything <i>that will be</i> after him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>I have seen everything during my <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17445W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17445W\"></sup>lifetime of futility; there is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17445X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17445X\"></sup>a righteous man who perishes in his righteousness and there is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17445Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17445Y\"></sup>a wicked man who prolongs <i>his life</i> in his wickedness.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Do not be excessively <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17446Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17446Z\"></sup>righteous and do not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17446AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17446AA\"></sup>be overly wise. Why should you ruin yourself?",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Do not be excessively wicked and do not be a fool. Why should you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17447AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17447AB\"></sup>die before your time?",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>It is good that you grasp one thing and also not let go of the other; for the one who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17448AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17448AC\"></sup>fears God comes forth with both of them.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17449AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17449AD\"></sup>Wisdom strengthens a wise man more than ten rulers who are in a city.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Indeed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17450AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17450AE\"></sup>there is not a righteous man on earth who <i>continually</i> does good and who never sins.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Also, do not take seriously all words which are spoken, so that you will not hear your servant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17451AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17451AF\"></sup>cursing you.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For you also have realized that you likewise have many times cursed others.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>I tested all this with wisdom, <i>and</i> I said, “I will be wise,” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17453AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17453AG\"></sup>but it was far from me.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>What has been is remote and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17454AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17454AH\"></sup>exceedingly mysterious. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17454AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17454AI\"></sup>Who can discover it?",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17455AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17455AJ\"></sup>directed my mind to know, to investigate and to seek wisdom and an explanation, and to know the evil of folly and the foolishness of madness.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And I discovered more <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17456AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17456AK\"></sup>bitter than death the woman whose heart is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17456AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17456AL\"></sup>snares and nets, whose hands are chains. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17456AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17456AM\"></sup>One who is pleasing to God will escape from her, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17456AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17456AN\"></sup>the sinner will be captured by her.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“Behold, I have discovered this,” says the Preacher, “<i>adding</i> one thing to another to find an explanation,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>which I am still seeking but have not found. I have found one man among a thousand, but I have not found a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17458AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17458AO\"></sup>woman among all these.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Behold, I have found only this, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17459AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17459AP\"></sup>God made men upright, but they have sought out many devices.”"
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>Who is like the wise man and who knows the interpretation of a matter? A man’s wisdom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17460A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17460A\"></sup>illumines him and causes his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17460B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17460B\"></sup>stern face to beam.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I say, “Keep the command of the king because of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17461C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17461C\"></sup>oath before God.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Do not be in a hurry <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17462D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17462D\"></sup>to leave him. Do not join in an evil matter, for he will do whatever he pleases.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Since the word of the king is authoritative, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17463E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17463E\"></sup>who will say to him, “What are you doing?”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17464F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17464F\"></sup>keeps a <i>royal</i> command <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17464G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17464G\"></sup>experiences no trouble, for a wise heart knows the proper time and procedure.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17465H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17465H\"></sup>there is a proper time and procedure for every delight, though a man’s trouble is heavy upon him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>If no one <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17466I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17466I\"></sup>knows what will happen, who can tell him when it will happen?",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17467J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17467J\"></sup>No man has authority to restrain the wind with the wind, or authority over the day of death; and there is no discharge in the time of war, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17467K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17467K\"></sup>evil will not deliver those who practice it.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>All this I have seen and applied my mind to every deed that has been done under the sun wherein a man has exercised <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17468L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17468L\"></sup>authority over <i>another</i> man to his hurt.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So then, I have seen the wicked buried, those who used to go in and out from the holy place, and they are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17469M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17469M\"></sup><i>soon</i> forgotten in the city where they did thus. This too is futility.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Because the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17470N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17470N\"></sup>sentence against an evil deed is not executed quickly, therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17470O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17470O\"></sup>the hearts of the sons of men among them are given fully to do evil.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Although a sinner does evil a hundred <i>times</i> and may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17471P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17471P\"></sup>lengthen his <i>life</i>, still I know that it will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17471Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17471Q\"></sup>well for those who fear God, who fear Him openly.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But it will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17472R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17472R\"></sup>not be well for the evil man and he will not lengthen his days like a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17472S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17472S\"></sup>shadow, because he does not fear God.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>There is futility which is done on the earth, that is, there are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17473T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17473T\"></sup>righteous men to whom it happens according to the deeds of the wicked. On the other hand, there are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17473U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17473U\"></sup>evil men to whom it happens according to the deeds of the righteous. I say that this too is futility.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So I commended pleasure, for there is nothing good for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17474V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17474V\"></sup>a man under the sun except to eat and to drink and to be merry, and this will stand by him in his toils <i>throughout</i> the days of his life which God has given him under the sun.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17475W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17475W\"></sup>gave my heart to know wisdom and to see the task which has been done on the earth (even though one should <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17475X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17475X\"></sup>never sleep day or night),",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and I saw every work of God, <i>I concluded</i> that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17476Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17476Y\"></sup>man cannot discover the work which has been done under the sun. Even though man should seek laboriously, he will not discover; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17476Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17476Z\"></sup>though the wise man should say, “I know,” he cannot discover."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>For I have taken all this to my heart and explain it that righteous men, wise men, and their deeds are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17477A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17477A\"></sup>in the hand of God. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17477B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17477B\"></sup>Man does not know whether <i>it will be</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17477C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17477C\"></sup>love or hatred; anything awaits him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17478D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17478D\"></sup>It is the same for all. There is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17478E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17478E\"></sup>one fate for the righteous and for the wicked; for the good, for the clean and for the unclean; for the man who offers a sacrifice and for the one who does not sacrifice. As the good man is, so is the sinner; as the swearer is, so is the one who is afraid to swear.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>This is an evil in all that is done under the sun, that there is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17479F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17479F\"></sup>one fate for all men. Furthermore, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17479G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17479G\"></sup>the hearts of the sons of men are full of evil and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17479H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17479H\"></sup>insanity is in their hearts throughout their lives. Afterwards they <i>go</i> to the dead.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For whoever is joined with all the living, there is hope; surely a live dog is better than a dead lion.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For the living know they will die; but the dead <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17481I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17481I\"></sup>do not know anything, nor have they any longer a reward, for their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17481J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17481J\"></sup>memory is forgotten.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Indeed their love, their hate and their zeal have already perished, and they will no longer have a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17482K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17482K\"></sup>share in all that is done under the sun.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Go <i>then</i>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17483L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17483L\"></sup>eat your bread in happiness and drink your wine with a cheerful heart; for God has already approved your works.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Let your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17484M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17484M\"></sup>clothes be white all the time, and let not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17484N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17484N\"></sup>oil be lacking on your head.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Enjoy life with the woman whom you love all the days of your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17485O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17485O\"></sup>fleeting life which He has given to you under the sun; for this is your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17485P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17485P\"></sup>reward in life and in your toil in which you have labored under the sun.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Whatever your hand finds to do, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17486Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17486Q\"></sup>do <i>it</i> with <i>all</i> your might; for there is no <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17486R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17486R\"></sup>activity or planning or knowledge or wisdom in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17486S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17486S\"></sup>Sheol where you are going.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>I again saw under the sun that the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17487T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17487T\"></sup>race is not to the swift and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17487U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17487U\"></sup>battle is not to the warriors, and neither is bread to the wise nor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17487V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17487V\"></sup>wealth to the discerning nor favor to men of ability; for time and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17487W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17487W\"></sup>chance overtake them all.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Moreover, man does not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17488X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17488X\"></sup>know his time: like fish caught in a treacherous net and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17488Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17488Y\"></sup>birds trapped in a snare, so the sons of men are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17488Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17488Z\"></sup>ensnared at an evil time when it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17488AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17488AA\"></sup>suddenly falls on them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Also this I came to see as wisdom under the sun, and it impressed me.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>There <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17490AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17490AB\"></sup>was a small city with few men in it and a great king came to it, surrounded it and constructed large siegeworks against it.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But there was found in it a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17491AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17491AC\"></sup>poor wise man and he delivered the city <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17491AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17491AD\"></sup>by his wisdom. Yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17491AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17491AE\"></sup>no one remembered that poor man.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So I said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17492AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17492AF\"></sup>Wisdom is better than strength.” But the wisdom of the poor man is despised and his words are not heeded.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17493AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17493AG\"></sup>words of the wise heard in quietness are <i>better</i> than the shouting of a ruler among fools.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17494AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17494AH\"></sup>Wisdom is better than weapons of war, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17494AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17494AI\"></sup>one sinner destroys much good."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>Dead flies make a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17495A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17495A\"></sup>perfumer’s oil stink, so a little foolishness is weightier than wisdom <i>and</i> honor.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>A wise man’s heart <i>directs him</i> toward the right, but the foolish <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17496B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17496B\"></sup>man’s heart <i>directs him</i> toward the left.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Even when the fool walks along the road, his sense is lacking and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17497C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17497C\"></sup>demonstrates to everyone <i>that</i> he is a fool.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>If the ruler’s temper rises against you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17498D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17498D\"></sup>do not abandon your position, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17498E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17498E\"></sup>composure allays great offenses.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>There is an evil I have seen under the sun, like an error which goes forth from the ruler—",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17500F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17500F\"></sup>folly is set in many exalted places while rich men sit in humble places.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I have seen <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17501G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17501G\"></sup>slaves <i>riding</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17501H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17501H\"></sup>on horses and princes walking like slaves on the land.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17502I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17502I\"></sup>He who digs a pit may fall into it, and a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17502J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17502J\"></sup>serpent may bite him who breaks through a wall.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He who quarries stones may be hurt by them, and he who splits logs may be endangered by them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>If the axe is dull and he does not sharpen <i>its</i> edge, then he must exert more strength. Wisdom has the advantage of giving success.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>If the serpent bites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17505K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17505K\"></sup>before being charmed, there is no profit for the charmer.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17506L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17506L\"></sup>Words from the mouth of a wise man are gracious, while the lips of a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17506M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17506M\"></sup>fool consume him;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>the beginning of his talking is folly and the end of it is wicked <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17507N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17507N\"></sup>madness.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Yet the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17508O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17508O\"></sup>fool multiplies words. No man knows what will happen, and who can tell him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17508P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17508P\"></sup>what will come after him?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The toil of a fool <i>so</i> wearies him that he does not <i>even</i> know how to go to a city.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Woe to you, O land, whose <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17510Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17510Q\"></sup>king is a lad and whose princes feast in the morning.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Blessed are you, O land, whose king is of nobility and whose princes eat at the appropriate time—for strength and not for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17511R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17511R\"></sup>drunkenness.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Through <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17512S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17512S\"></sup>indolence the rafters sag, and through slackness the house leaks.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><i>Men</i> prepare a meal for enjoyment, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17513T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17513T\"></sup>wine makes life merry, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17513U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17513U\"></sup>money is the answer to everything.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Furthermore, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17514V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17514V\"></sup>in your bedchamber do not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17514W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17514W\"></sup>curse a king, and in your sleeping rooms do not curse a rich man, for a bird of the heavens will carry the sound and the winged creature will make the matter known."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17515A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17515A\"></sup>Cast your bread on the surface of the waters, for you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17515B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17515B\"></sup>will find it after many days.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17516C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17516C\"></sup>Divide your portion to seven, or even to eight, for you do not know what <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17516D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17516D\"></sup>misfortune may occur on the earth.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>If the clouds are full, they pour out rain upon the earth; and whether a tree falls toward the south or toward the north, wherever the tree falls, there it lies.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He who watches the wind will not sow and he who looks at the clouds will not reap.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Just as you do not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17519E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17519E\"></sup>know the path of the wind and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17519F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17519F\"></sup>how bones <i>are formed</i> in the womb of the pregnant woman, so you do not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17519G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17519G\"></sup>know the activity of God who makes all things.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Sow your seed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17520H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17520H\"></sup>in the morning and do not be idle in the evening, for you do not know whether morning or evening sowing will succeed, or whether both of them alike will be good.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The light is pleasant, and <i>it is</i> good for the eyes to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17521I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17521I\"></sup>see the sun.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Indeed, if a man should live many years, let him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17522J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17522J\"></sup>rejoice in them all, and let him remember the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17522K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17522K\"></sup>days of darkness, for they will be many. Everything that is to come <i>will be</i> futility.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Rejoice, young man, during your childhood, and let your heart be pleasant during the days of young manhood. And follow the impulses of your heart and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17523L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17523L\"></sup>desires of your eyes. Yet know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17523M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17523M\"></sup>God will bring you to judgment for all these things.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So, remove grief and anger from your heart and put away <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17524N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17524N\"></sup>pain from your body, because childhood and the prime of life are fleeting."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17525A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17525A\"></sup>Remember also your Creator in the days of your youth, before the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17525B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17525B\"></sup>evil days come and the years draw near when you will say, “I have no delight in them”;",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>before the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17526C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17526C\"></sup>sun and the light, the moon and the stars are darkened, and clouds return after the rain;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>in the day that the watchmen of the house tremble, and mighty men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17527D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17527D\"></sup>stoop, the grinding ones stand idle because they are few, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17527E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17527E\"></sup>those who look through windows grow dim;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and the doors on the street are shut as the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17528F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17528F\"></sup>sound of the grinding mill is low, and one will arise at the sound of the bird, and all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17528G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17528G\"></sup>daughters of song will sing softly.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Furthermore, men are afraid of a high place and of terrors on the road; the almond tree blossoms, the grasshopper drags himself along, and the caperberry is ineffective. For man goes to his eternal <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17529H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17529H\"></sup>home while <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17529I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17529I\"></sup>mourners go about in the street.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><i>Remember Him</i> before the silver cord is broken and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17530J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17530J\"></sup>golden bowl is crushed, the pitcher by the well is shattered and the wheel at the cistern is crushed;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>then the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17531K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17531K\"></sup>dust will return to the earth as it was, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17531L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17531L\"></sup>spirit will return to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17531M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17531M\"></sup>God who gave it.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17532N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17532N\"></sup>Vanity of vanities,” says the Preacher, “all is vanity!”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>In addition to being a wise man, the Preacher also taught the people knowledge; and he pondered, searched out and arranged <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17533O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17533O\"></sup>many proverbs.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The Preacher sought to find <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17534P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17534P\"></sup>delightful words and to write <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17534Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17534Q\"></sup>words of truth correctly.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17535R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17535R\"></sup>words of wise men are like <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17535S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17535S\"></sup>goads, and masters of <i>these</i> collections are like well-driven <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17535T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17535T\"></sup>nails; they are given by one Shepherd.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But beyond this, my son, be warned: the writing of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17536U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17536U\"></sup>many books is endless, and excessive <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17536V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17536V\"></sup>devotion <i>to books</i> is wearying to the body.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The conclusion, when all has been heard, <i>is</i>: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17537W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17537W\"></sup>fear God and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17537X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17537X\"></sup>keep His commandments, because this <i>applies to</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17537Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17537Y\"></sup>every person.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17538Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17538Z\"></sup>God will bring every act to judgment, everything which is hidden, whether it is good or evil."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;